  "prompt": "What is it like to live in Spain for an Indian?",
  "response": "Living in Spain as an Indian can be a unique experience with both challenges and opportunities:\n\nPositive Aspects:\n1. Cultural diversity and welcoming environment\n2. Generally friendly and warm Spanish people\n3. Beautiful landscapes and rich cultural heritage\n4. High quality of life\n5. Good healthcare system\n6. Affordable cost of living compared to some other European countries\n7. Mediterranean climate\n8. Great food and lifestyle\n\nChallenges:\n1. Language barrier (Spanish or Catalan required)\n2. Different work culture and professional expectations\n3. Initial difficulty in networking and finding jobs\n4. Potential cultural adaptation challenges\n5. Lower salaries compared to some other European countries\n6. Bureaucratic processes can be complex\n7. Limited Indian communities in some cities\n\nProfessional Considerations:\n1. Tech and IT sectors have good opportunities\n2. Teaching English is a common job for expats\n3. Startup ecosystem is developing\n4. Knowledge of Spanish significantly improves job prospects\n\nSocial Life:\n1. Vibrant social culture\n2. Late-night dining and socializing\n3. Opportunities to meet international communities\n4. Relatively open and progressive society\n\nLiving conditions generally depend on the specific city (Madrid, Barcelona, Valencia) and individual circumstances, but overall, many Indians find Spain an attractive destination.",
